Artemis_Helios_Figures Documentation
Technical Documentation — Helios-Artemis IEEE Publication Figures
Hussain Touhid Siddiquee  |  Dept. EEE, Leading University Sylhet  |  Helios-Artemis Research Project

1. Purpose
gen_figures_hires.py generates all nine publication-quality figures required for the Helios-Artemis MPPT paper submission. Every figure targets the IEEE two-column format at 300 DPI using Times New Roman typography. The script is fully self-contained — it does not depend on simulation output files from MATLAB. Instead it re-implements the core physics models (irradiance, PV, P&O) and uses fixed random seeds so figures are exactly reproducible across machines and runs.

2. Quick-Start
Run from the project root directory:
pip install numpy matplotlib scipy
python gen_figures_hires.py

Output is written to a figures/ subdirectory created automatically adjacent to the script. Each figure is saved as a PNG at 300 DPI.
NOTE  matplotlib backend is set to 'Agg' at the top of the file. Do not remove this line — without it the script will fail on headless servers (CI, SSH sessions, WSL without display).

3. Global Configuration
3.1  Canvas & Font Settings
Parameter	Value / Notes
Column widths (C1, C2)	3.5 in (single column), 7.16 in (full two-column) — IEEE standard
Font family	serif → ['Times New Roman', 'DejaVu Serif'] fallback
Base font size	8 pt (axis labels), 8.5 pt (titles), 7 pt (ticks/legends)
Line width	1.0 pt (data lines), 0.6 pt (axis spines), 0.35 pt (grid)
DPI	300 for both display and savefig
Padding	savefig.bbox='tight', pad_inches=0.04 — minimal whitespace
3.2  Colour Palette
Variable	Hex	Usage
B	#1565C0	Primary blue — irradiance, measured data, primary bars
R	#C62828	Red — baselines, envelope curves, alarm/peak values
G	#2E7D32	Green — Helios-Artemis results, battery/SoC
O	#E65100	Orange — warnings, cost comparisons, literature bands
P	#6A1B9A	Purple — LSTM/prediction, step-size law, η traces
GR	#546E7A	Grey — secondary text, plain P&O baseline
3.3  Random Seeds
Seed	Scope	Purpose
np.random.seed(23)	Global (top of file)	Controls all stochastic content in fig2, fig5, fig7
np.random.seed(7)	Local in fig4()	Generates LSTM test-set irradiance independently of global seed
WARN  The fig4 suptitle hard-codes R²=0.917, MAE=50.7 W m⁻² (paper-reported values). The live-computed metrics from seed=7 will differ slightly. This is a cosmetic mismatch only — the subplot (a) title shows the live values correctly.

4. Shared Physics Helper: pv_model()
A single PV model function is shared by fig3, fig5, and fig7 to ensure consistency across all figures that show PV output. It implements the same IEC 61215 power-law model used in ha_pv_v3.m.
Argument / Return	Description
G	Irradiance (W m⁻²)
Vr	Reference/operating voltage (V)
Isc0=2.91 A	STC short-circuit current (post-soiling: 3.0 × 0.97)
Voc0=21.6 V	STC open-circuit voltage
k=14.2606	I-V curve exponent — analytically fitted so I(Vmp)=Imp exactly
bV=−3.4×10⁻³ /°C	Voc temperature coefficient
aI=+0.5×10⁻³ /°C	Isc temperature coefficient
NOCT=45°C, Tamb=35°C	Thermal derating parameters
Returns: (Ppv, Pm, Vrc)	PV output power (W), true MPP power (W), clamped operating voltage (V)

